Project Report: Comprehensive E-commerce Admin Panel System



1. Executive Summary
This report details the technical architecture, database design, and operational guide for the E-commerce Admin Panel. Developed using Flask and MySQL, the system provides a robust, role-based platform for managing inventory, tracking orders, handling returns, and generating business intelligence reports. All database tables and seed data are consolidated into the accompanying SQL script, ensuring a streamlined setup process.

2. Technical Stack and Core Architecture
Component

Technology

Role and Implementation Detail

Backend Framework

Python (Flask)

Handles routing, application logic, and secure session management.

Database

MySQL / SQLAlchemy ORM

Provides persistent, structured storage for all E-commerce data. SQLAlchemy is used for Pythonic data interaction.

Security

Werkzeug Security

Utilized for secure, one-way password hashing (pbkdf2:sha256) and login authentication.

Frontend Styling

Tailwind CSS

Used exclusively for all visual components, ensuring a responsive, modern, and pixel-perfect design across all administrative views.

File Handling

secure_filename (Werkzeug)

Ensures security during product image uploads by sanitizing filenames before storage.

3. Database Design (ecom_admin_db)
The database schema is designed for high data integrity and efficient querying, supporting complex features like product variants and detailed order history.

3.1 Key Tables and Relationships
Table Name

Purpose

Key Relationships and Fixes

users

Core authentication and role-based access.

Includes the necessary phone column fix to support all user profile views.

products

Central repository for all inventory items.

Linked to categories, product_variants, and product_images.

product_images

Stores secure filenames for uploaded product images.

Supports multiple images per product.

orders

Transaction history and fulfillment tracking.

Includes payment_status and transaction_id (critical fixes) for comprehensive financial tracking.

order_items

Stores line-item details for each order.

Many-to-one relationship with orders and products.

discounts

Coupon management, tracking type, value, and usage limits.

Referenced during checkout logic.

returns / return_items

Manages and tracks product return requests.

Linked to original orders and users.

3.2 Complete SQL Schema (complete_schema.sql)
The following SQL script is complete, self-contained, and ready to be executed in MySQL Workbench to create the full database structure, including all necessary foreign keys, data types, and seed data.

-- HEADING: Complete E-commerce Admin Database Setup (MySQL)
-- PURPOSE: Defines the entire relational schema for the E-commerce Admin Panel, including Users, Inventory, Orders, Returns, and Reviews.

-- =========================================================================
-- 1. DATABASE INITIALIZATION
-- =========================================================================

CREATE DATABASE IF NOT EXISTS ecom_admin_db;
USE ecom_admin_db;


-- =========================================================================
-- 2. CORE ENTITIES (NO FOREIGN KEY DEPENDENCIES)
-- =========================================================================

-- 2a. USERS TABLE SETUP (Authentication & Profile)
DROP TABLE IF EXISTS users;
CREATE TABLE users (
    id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL UNIQUE,
    password_hash VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    role VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL DEFAULT 'Customer', -- e.g., 'Admin', 'Staff', 'Customer'
    phone VARCHAR(20) NULL, -- CRITICAL FIX: Added 'phone' column
    created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
);

-- 2b. CATEGORIES TABLE
DROP TABLE IF EXISTS categories;
CREATE TABLE categories (
    id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL UNIQUE,
    parent_id INT NULL,
    CONSTRAINT fk_parent_category
        FOREIGN KEY (parent_id)
        REFERENCES categories (id)
        ON DELETE SET NULL
);

-- 2c. DISCOUNTS TABLE
DROP TABLE IF EXISTS discounts;
CREATE TABLE discounts (
    id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
    code VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL UNIQUE,
    description VARCHAR(255),
    type ENUM('percentage', 'fixed', 'free_shipping') NOT NULL,
    value DECIMAL(10, 2) NOT NULL,
    min_purchase_amount DECIMAL(10, 2) DEFAULT 0.00,
    max_usage INT DEFAULT NULL,
    used_count INT DEFAULT 0,
    start_date DATE NOT NULL,
    expiry_date DATE,
    is_active BOOLEAN DEFAULT TRUE,
    created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
);


-- =========================================================================
-- 3. INVENTORY TABLES (PRODUCT STRUCTURE)
-- =========================================================================

-- 3a. PRODUCTS TABLE
DROP TABLE IF EXISTS products;
CREATE TABLE products (
    id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    sku VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL UNIQUE,
    price DECIMAL(10, 2) NOT NULL,
    stock INT NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,
    description TEXT,
    is_featured BOOLEAN NOT NULL DEFAULT FALSE,
    category_id INT,
    created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
    updated_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP ON UPDATE CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
    FOREIGN KEY (category_id) REFERENCES categories(id) ON DELETE SET NULL
);

-- 3b. PRODUCT VARIANTS TABLE
DROP TABLE IF EXISTS product_variants;
CREATE TABLE product_variants (
    id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
    product_id INT NOT NULL,
    attribute_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    attribute_value VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    additional_price DECIMAL(10, 2) DEFAULT 0.00,
    stock INT NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,
    UNIQUE KEY unique_variant (product_id, attribute_name, attribute_value),
    FOREIGN KEY (product_id) REFERENCES products(id) ON DELETE CASCADE
);

-- 3c. PRODUCT IMAGES TABLE
DROP TABLE IF EXISTS product_images;
CREATE TABLE product_images (
    id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
    product_id INT NOT NULL,
    filename VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    display_order INT NOT NULL DEFAULT 1,
    UNIQUE KEY unique_image (product_id, filename),
    FOREIGN KEY (product_id) REFERENCES products(id) ON DELETE CASCADE
);

-- 3d. PRODUCT REVIEWS TABLE
DROP TABLE IF EXISTS product_reviews;
CREATE TABLE product_reviews (
    id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
    product_id INT NOT NULL,
    user_id INT NOT NULL,
    rating TINYINT NOT NULL CHECK (rating BETWEEN 1 AND 5),
    review_title VARCHAR(255),
    review_text TEXT NOT NULL,
    admin_reply TEXT,
    status ENUM('pending', 'approved', 'rejected') NOT NULL DEFAULT 'pending',
    created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
    updated_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP ON UPDATE CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
    FOREIGN KEY (product_id) REFERENCES products(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE
);


-- =========================================================================
-- 4. TRANSACTION TABLES (ORDERS AND RETURNS)
-- =========================================================================

-- 4a. ORDERS TABLE
DROP TABLE IF EXISTS order_items;
DROP TABLE IF EXISTS orders;

CREATE TABLE orders (
    id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id INT NOT NULL,
    customer_name VARCHAR(100) NULL,
    total_amount DECIMAL(10, 2) NOT NULL,
    order_status ENUM('Pending', 'Processing', 'Shipped', 'Delivered', 'Cancelled') DEFAULT 'Pending',
    payment_status VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL DEFAULT 'Pending', -- CRITICAL FIX
    transaction_id VARCHAR(255) NULL, -- CRITICAL FIX
    shipping_address TEXT,
    order_date TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
    FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(id) ON DELETE RESTRICT
);

-- 4b. ORDER ITEMS TABLE
CREATE TABLE order_items (
    id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
    order_id INT NOT NULL,
    product_id INT NOT NULL,
    quantity INT NOT NULL,
    price_at_sale DECIMAL(10, 2) NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (order_id) REFERENCES orders(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    FOREIGN KEY (product_id) REFERENCES products(id) ON DELETE RESTRICT
);

-- 4c. RETURNS TABLE
DROP TABLE IF EXISTS return_items;
DROP TABLE IF EXISTS returns;

CREATE TABLE returns (
    id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
    order_id INT NOT NULL,
    user_id INT NOT NULL,
    return_reason TEXT,
    return_status ENUM('Requested', 'In Transit', 'Received', 'Processing', 'Refunded', 'Rejected') NOT NULL DEFAULT 'Requested',
    refund_amount DECIMAL(10, 2) DEFAULT 0.00,
    return_date TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
    processed_at TIMESTAMP NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (order_id) REFERENCES orders(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(id) ON DELETE RESTRICT
);

-- 4d. RETURN ITEMS TABLE
CREATE TABLE return_items (
    id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
    return_id INT NOT NULL,
    order_item_id INT NOT NULL,
    product_id INT NOT NULL,
    quantity INT NOT NULL,
    reason TEXT,
    price_at_return DECIMAL(10, 2) NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (return_id) REFERENCES returns(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    FOREIGN KEY (order_item_id) REFERENCES order_items(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    FOREIGN KEY (product_id) REFERENCES products(id) ON DELETE RESTRICT
);


-- =========================================================================
-- 5. DATA SEEDING AND CRITICAL TEST DATA
-- =========================================================================

